Statement (at most 750 characters):

Mike and Sam study Belyi maps, represented graphically by dessins d’enfants. Aaron studies flat surfaces. When we met at ICERM’s Illustrating Mathematics semester in fall 2019, we started asking whether we could draw better pictures of Belyi maps by taking advantage of their flat geometry. We’re looking not only for aesthetic appeal, but also for a new perspective on an old question: which Belyi maps are related by symmetries of the algebraic numbers that define them? Is this reflected in their dessins d’enfants? We hope the right visualization might reveal hidden patterns in the symmetry relationship.

