Title: Who wants to be a Belyionaire?

Medium: Magma, SageMath, GLSL, HTML / CSS / JavaScript

Year of completion: 2021

Description (at most 750 characters):

A central goal of number theory is to understand the symmetries of algebraic numbers. One way these symmetries reveal themselves is by acting on deceptively simple drawings called “dessins d’enfants.” This piece is a challenge for all of us at Bridges: can we tell which dessins are related by symmetries just by looking at them? We’ve drawn some collections of Belyi maps from a database; you’re invited to try your hand at sorting them into their symmetry classes. If you succeed, you might just become... a Belyionaire.

The pictures were painted with a GLSL shader, using power series and symmetry data computed in SageMath and Magma. Ideas and methods came from papers by Klug, Musty, Schiavone & Voight (2014) and Mulase & Penkava (1998).

URL for digital media submissions or this artwork: https://vectornaut.github.io/chorno-belyi
